items.title: Visiting Ours

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E07.In God We Trust.mkv
items.summary: Michael attempts to fire the family's incompetent, but likeable attorney. George Michael impresses Maeby with a muscle suit for a "Living Classics" pagent. Tobias has a psychological affliction where he is unable to take off his clothes.
items.title: In God We Trust

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E08.My Mother, The Car.mkv
items.summary: Michael loses his short-term memory, which Lucille uses to her advantage. Gob attempts to use the family yacht before Michael sells it. George Michael and Maeby attempt to see an R-rated movie about cousins having an affair. Buster and Lucille 2 take "the next step".
items.title: My Mother, the Car

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E09.Storming the Castle.mkv
items.summary: Michael cannot go through with his plan to break up Gob and Marta. A thug magician wants to take Gob's "legs". Maeby wears all leather to get back at her mother, and Lucille decides to confront Buster's relationship with Lucille 2.
items.title: Storming the Castle

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E10.Pier Pressure.mkv
items.summary: Buster realizes that medical marijuana will help cure Lucille 2's vertigo, and pays George Michael to get it for him from Gob. Lindsay sends Maeby to spend a day with Lucille to punish her for bad grades. Michael thinks George Michael is on drugs and attempts to teach him a lesson.
items.title: Pier Pressure

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E11.Public Relations.mkv
items.summary: When George Michael is a rejected by a private school due to the family's reputation, Michael hires a publicist from his gym who he's been flirting with to change the public perspective of the Bluths. Meanwhile, Tobias is sent to Boston to reclaim his medical license.
items.title: Public Relations

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E12.Marta Complex.mkv
items.summary: When Lucille throws an anniversary party for Tobias and Lindsay on Valentine's Day, Michael gives an impassioned speech about love. This makes Marta realize she has feelings for him and Lindsay realize she wants a divorce. Meanwhile, Buster decides to move out of the penthouse and Lucille revels in living alone for the first time.
items.title: Marta Complex

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E13.Beef Consomme.mkv
items.summary: After learning that Marta has feelings for him, Michael goes to her and they decide to get permission from Gob before taking things to the next level. Meanwhile, Lindsay and Tobias finally get to the heart of his "never-nude" problem and George Sr. faces his first hearing.
items.title: Beef ConsommÃ©

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E14.Shock and Aww.mkv
items.summary: Michael falls for his George Michael's ethics teacher, whom his son also has a crush on. Meanwhile, Lucille adopts a 14-year old Korean boy, and George Sr.'s "Caged Wisdom" tapes have given him a new admirer.
items.title: Shock and Aww

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E15.Staff Infection.mkv
items.summary: When Michael discovers his family has been receiving paychecks without working, he forces them all to get jobs within the company. Lindsay questions his management skills, and Tobias checks himself in at George Sr.'s prison to research a film role.
items.title: Staff Infection

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E16.Altar Egos.mkv
items.summary: Michael attempts to have a one-night stand with an attorney whom he doesn't know is not only blind, but the prosecutor who is trying to put his father in jail. Also, Gob gets married on a dare, Maeby pretends to be a girl with a made up disease, and George Sr.'s admirer turns out to be an undercover SEC agent who has truly fallen for him.
items.title: Altar Egos

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E17.Justice Is Blind.mkv
items.summary: Gob steals a file on the government's case against the Bluth Company that Maggie had given to Michael. Tobias is sent to Maggie's house to get evidence, George Michael tries to prove Maeby's fraud, and Lindsay fights to remove the Ten Commandments from the courthouse lawn.
items.title: Justice Is Blind

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E18.Missing Kitty.mkv
items.summary: Gob attempts to make good on his promise to make the family yacht disappear. Meanwhile, Lindsay and Maeby try to track down Lindsay's grandmother, Tobias seeks George Sr.'s respect, and Michael attempts to fire Kitty, who claims to have information that could bring down the company.
items.title: Missing Kitty

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E19.Best Man for the Gob.mkv
items.summary: George Sr. uses Gob's bachelor party as an opportunity to set up his accountant in a compromising position so that he can blackmail him.  Meanwhile, Michael tries to prove he's a fun guy, and the Funkes reunite their family folk-music band.
items.title: Best Man for the Gob

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E20.Whistler's Mother.mkv
items.summary: Michael deals with numerous requests for some unfrozen money, and chastises Lucille for being too coddling with Buster. Lindsay decides to protest the war to boost her self esteem while Tobias and Gob decide to start a coffee company.
items.title: Whistler's Mother

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E21.Not Without My Daughter.mkv
items.summary: Michael takes Maeby to work with him on Take Your Daughter to Work Day. After being slighted by Michael, Tobias, George-Michael and Gob all go to the mall to prove that they are just manly. Oscar takes Lucille and Buster to Annyong's soccer game.
items.title: Not Without My Daughter

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 1/Arrested Development.S01E22.Let 'Em Eat Cake.mkv
items.summary: In the first season finale, George Sr. has a heart attack, and Maeby is jealous when George Michael likes another girl. Meanwhile, Lindsay decides to leave Tobias until a book he wrote a long time ago becomes a gay bestseller, and Buster and Annyong compete over women.
items.title: Let 'Em Eat Cake

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E01.The One Where Michael Leaves.mkv
items.summary: Michael and George Michael leave for Phoenix but go back to ensure the family misses them. Lindsay wants to have an open marriage, which causes Tobias to try to join the Blue Man Group under the impression that they are a support group for depressed men. Lucille signs Buster up for the Army after being goaded by a Michael Moore look-alike. Gob becomes president of the Bluth Company.
items.title: The One Where Michael Leaves

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E02.The One Where They Build a House.mkv
items.summary: Michael is driven crazy by Gob when he impresses the board as the new company figurehead due to Michael's legal troubles. Meanwhile, George Sr. is arrested in Mexico for a crime Oscar committed, and Buster witnesses something that utterly shocks him.
items.title: The One Where They Build a House
items.titleSort: One Where They Build a House

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E03.Â¡Amigos!.mkv
items.summary: Michael is increasingly frustrated over being abandoned by the family, and when the staircar is found in Mexico, Michael vows to find his father and give him a piece of his mind. Also, Buster spends time with Lupe's family and thinks he's in Mexico.
items.title: Amigos

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E04.Good Grief.mkv
items.summary: Lucille hires a bounty hunter, Ice, to find George Sr., who may be closer than everyone thinks. Gob tries to pull off an elaborate illusion, Maeby tries to set Lindsay up with Ice, and Michael tries to mend George Michael's broken relationship.
items.title: Good Grief

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E05.Sad Sack.mkv
items.summary: George Sr. fears he's losing Lucille to Oscar. Gob motivates Buster for the Army while Lindsay spends more time with Maeby to get closer to Steve Holt and Tobias starts working out.
items.title: Sad Sack

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E06.Afternoon Delight.mkv
items.summary: Gob stages mass firings after being inadvertently roasted at the Bluth Company Christmas party. Michael is forced to rebuild the Banana Stand, and Buster plays hooky from the Army at an arcade game.
items.title: Afternoon Delight

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E07.Switch Hitter.mkv
items.summary: The Bluths rival development company hires Gob, who finds the company president a father figure, in preparation for the Bluth-Sitwell softball game; Lindsay hallucinates from taking anti-depressants.
items.title: Switch Hitter

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E08.Queen for a Day.mkv
items.summary: Michael sells a portion of his stock in the Bluth company to buy a car, and Lucille 2 returns, only to discover that Buster is dating the company secretary Starla.
items.title: Queen for a Day

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E09.Burning Love.mkv
items.summary: Michael reunites with his long, lost love Sally Sitwell, but faces interference from parents. Meanwhile, the two Lucilles need someone to bid on them at the bachelorette auction with Buster already in a relationship.
items.title: Burning Love

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E10.Ready, Aim, Marry Me!.mkv
items.summary: With the company in dire financial straits and the Bluths no longer the primary shareholders, Michael must turn to old family friend "Uncle" Jack Dorso for financial assistance. Uncle Jack, however, wants something in return.
items.title: Ready, Aim, Marry Me

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E11.Out on a Limb.mkv
items.summary: Just as Michael's relationship with Sally starts to flourish, Maggie Lizer returns nine months pregnant, and Michael immediately assumes he's the father. George Michael attempts to break up with Ann, and Buster learns he's being deployed to Iraq.
items.title: Out on a Limb

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E12.Hand to God.mkv
items.summary: Michael tries to find out who's the father of Maggie's baby, or if it's just another of her lies; Gob tries to find out whether he was responsible for Buster's accident.
items.title: Hand to God

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E13.Motherboy XXX.mkv
items.summary: Lucille abducts George Michael for a mother-son dance, Buster adjusts to having a hook for a hand and Gob reunites with his estranged wife. Also, Tobias stars as George Sr. in a biopic about the Bluth family, which causes Lindsay to become more attracted to him.
items.title: Motherboy XXX

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E14.The Immaculate Election.mkv
items.summary: George Michael runs for student body president, which Gob manages to ruin. Buster has an affair with Lupe, who is being sought after by Lindsay and Tobias attempts to move out of the model home, then develops a new persona when he regrets his decision.
items.title: The Immaculate Election

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E15.Sword of Destiny.mkv
items.summary: Gob and Buster team up for some magic tricks with the help of Buster's fake hand, but when Tony Wonder, a rival magician, starts to mentor them, somebody gets the finger. Meanwhile, Michael is forced to delegate some work when he's hospitalized and Lindsay teaches George Michael how to drive using the staircar.
items.title: Sword of Destiny

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E16.Meat the Veals.mkv
items.summary: George Sr. tries to find a way to attend an anniversary dinner for Lucille while Michael deliberately offends Ann's devout Christian parents. Tobias goes overboard performing his "Mrs. Featherbottom" persona.
items.title: Meat the Veals

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E17.Spring Breakout.mkv
items.summary: Gob confronts the editor of the videos that showcased his magic mistakes. Michael tricks Lucille in to rehab, and then attempts to get her out after George Sr. is kidnapped.
items.title: Spring Breakout

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 2/Arrested Development.S02E18.Righteous Brothers.mkv
items.summary: Gob hides George Sr. while the model home's plumbing is checked; George Michael helps Ann protest Maeby's new movie; Tobias takes a liking to Kitty after Michael asks him to keep an eye on her.
items.title: The Righteous Brothers

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E01.The Cabin Show.mkv
items.summary: Michael learns that it's actually George Sr.'s twin brother Oscar serving time in prison, not George. After getting a tip from Barry, Michael heads to Reno to find George, but that costs him a camping trip he promised his son.
items.title: The Cabin Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E02.For British Eyes Only.mkv
items.summary: Investigating his father's claim that a British group set him up, Michael goes to "Wee Britain" and is smitten with a beautiful woman named Rita. Lindsay attempts to seduce the new family attorney, and Gob goes to extremes to avoid his newly discovered son.
items.title: For British Eyes Only

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E03.Forget Me Now.mkv
items.summary: George Sr. is placed under house arrest by the family's new attorney Bob Loblaw, and finds that it's not exactly a walk in the park. Michael sets up his first date with Rita, but Rita has an unfortunate encounter with the family beforehand.
items.title: Forget-Me-Now

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E04.Notapusy.mkv
items.summary: To prove he's a man to Rita, Michael and his nephew Steve Holt compete in the Church And State Fair's annual triathlon. George Sr. tries to scare some at-risk youth, and Tobias tries to help George-Michael's girlfriend Ann to compete in the fairs' "inner beauty" pageant.
items.title: Notapusy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E05.Mr. F.mkv
items.summary: Michael must deal with a huge mole problem in order to salvage a major real estate deal with Japanese investors. In an effort to help Michael, Gob and Buster team up with George Sr.'s surrogate, Larry, to devise a plan and save the deal, but their plan falls apart in a big way. Meanwhile, Tobias mistakes a CIA agent for a CAA agent and inadvertently betrays the family, and Michael makes Rita a proposal she can't refuse. Frankie Muniz makes a cameo as himself.
items.title: Mr. F

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E06.The Ocean Walker.mkv
items.summary: After Michael announces he's marrying Rita, George Sr. worries that she's after the family's money. But when Rita's Uncle Trevor tries to stop the wedding by revealing some surprising information about Rita, Michael must decide if he wants to walk down the aisle.
items.title: The Ocean Walker

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E07.Prison Break-In.mkv
items.summary: The family plans their annual fund raiser, and they actually have a cause this time. Tobias is ailing due to his transplanted hair plugs, which appear to be rejecting him. Lindsay uses the illness as her ticket back into high society, and Michael learns of the prison warden's true intentions with his mother after reading the warden's screenplay.
items.title: Prison Break-In

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E08.Making a Stand.mkv
items.summary: Michael is tired of his father always having Gob compete with him, so Michael gets Gob his own banana stand franchise, only to find that Gob has set it up 20 feet from the old one. After the two compete, they decide to teach their father an elaborate lesson, and Buster refuses to use his handicap to scare kids. Meanwhile, Maeby uses Lucille's surgery in a horror film.
items.title: Making a Stand

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E09.S.O.B.s.mkv
items.summary: George Sr. suggests a last-ditch effort to save the family by holding a fund raiser to raise money to pay their legal expenses. Michael suggests to Lindsay that she take over the house work, and he sends George-Michael to an expensive boarding school. Meanwhile, Maeby has trouble with a snowboarding film and Tobias tries to be a "discipline daddy".
items.title: S.O.B.s

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E10.Fakin' It.mkv
items.summary: George, Sr. hires a new attorney who asks the Bluths to participate in a mock trial to help prepare them for the real thing. The attorney gets actor Judge Reinhold to preside over the mock case. Meanwhile, Buster fakes a coma to get out of testifying, and George Michael and Maeby participate in a mock wedding to entertain hospital patients. Back at the office, Michael discovers that he may have a long-lost sister named Nellie Bluth.
items.title: Fakin' It

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E11.Family Ties.mkv
items.summary: In an effort to get to the bottom of things, Michael tracks Nellie down and hires her as a consultant for the Bluth Co. Unfortunately, Michael discovers Nellie's hands-on approach is more than he bargained for.
items.title: Family Ties

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E12.Exit Strategy.mkv
items.summary: Gob goes to Iraq to perform his Christian magic act on the USO tour and ends up incarcerated. Michael learns George, Sr. sent Gob to Iraq to burn down the model home he built there, so Michael and Buster fly to Iraq to spring their brother from prison.
items.title: Exit Strategy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 3/Arrested Development.S03E13.Development Arrested.mkv
items.summary: After returning home from Iraq, George Sr. is finally cleared of all charges, and Michael is relieved to be the head of a successful company for a change. The real brains behind the madness is revealed, and just as the family begins to celebrate their victory, a whole new set of problems emerge.
items.title: Development Arrested

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E01.Flight of the Phoenix.mkv
items.summary: Michael says goodbye to the family business and starts his own. And the life of the family is turned upside down when their mail man Pete dies.
items.title: Flight of the Phoenix

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E02.Borderline Personalities.mkv
items.summary: George Sr. comes up with a get rich quick scam after his family falls apart.
items.title: Borderline Personalities

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E03.Indian Takers.mkv
items.summary: Lindsay tries to reclaim her sense of self while traveling and getting back to her political activist roots.
items.title: Indian Takers

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E04.The B. Team.mkv
items.summary: Michael is presented with a new business opportunity that could change his life, but unfortunately, he needs his family to sign off.
items.title: The B. Team

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E05.A New Start.mkv
items.summary: Tobias searches for meaning after splitting with Lindsay, only to find that old habits die hard.
items.title: A New Start

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E06.Double Crossers.mkv
items.summary: George Sr.'s new business hits a rough patch, and he must bribe a politician to get his scam back on track.
items.title: Double Crossers

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E07.Colony Collapse.mkv
items.summary: Gob finds a new group of friends after his relationship falls apart and his family abandons him.
items.title: Colony Collapse

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E08.Red Hairing.mkv
items.summary: Lindsay continues to push away from being a Bluth by embracing a relationship and finding a new career.
items.title: Red Hairing

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E09.Smashed.mkv
items.summary: Tobias returns to his roots and reunites with his leading lady after a rough few weeks.
items.title: Smashed

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E10.Queen B..mkv
items.summary: Lucille finds that her children have started dividing up her things, and adjusts to her new home.
items.title: Queen B.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E11.A New Attitude.mkv
items.summary: Gob accepts a job from his brother, but is distracted by a scheme of his own.
items.title: A New Attitude

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E12.SeÃ±oritis.mkv
items.summary: Maeby moves out on her own and reconnects with her cousin George-Michael.
items.title: SeÃ±oritis

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E13.It Gets Better.mkv
items.summary: At UC Irvine things get steamy when George-Michael finds himself in a love triangle with his best friend Ray and his girlfriend Becky.
items.title: It Gets Better

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E14.Off the Hook.mkv
items.summary: Buster struggles to make it on his own and break away from his overbearing mother.
items.title: Off the Hook

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 4/Arrested Development.S04E15.Blockheads.mkv
items.summary: George-Michael tries to reconnect with his father, but is finding himself overwhelmed by the responsibility of running his business.

items.summary: For varying reasons, most of the Bluths (even Steve Holt) feel compelled to run off to Mexico. Michael tries to convince Buster to go to the police.

items.summary: The Bluths receive/present their award, but it weighs on George Sr. and creates new problems. Michael and George-Michael have a deep conversation.

items.summary: Michael attempts to bail out Buster. George-Michael finally meets the Howards, and Ron informs Michael that his plans for the movie have changed.

items.summary: George-Michael thinks he's being lied to by Michael, who thinks he's being lied to by George Sr. Gob hires guys to help with his "closet conversion."

items.summary: As the Second of July parade approaches, Sally steps up her campaign against Lindsay while the Bluths again struggle to keep their stories straight.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Arrested Development/Season 5/Arrested.Development.S05E09.720p.WEB.x264-GalaxyTV.mkv
items.summary: Buster fails to show for his own prison release party. Michael examines company financial records. George-Michael seeks Anonymous help to deceive Rebel.

items.summary: Michael jumps at a chance to spend more time with George-Michael, who seeks a clueless president for Fakeblock. Tobias relocates his makeshift family.

In this parody of "It's A Wonderful Life", the duo are visited by his guardian angel, who shows Butt-Head that everyone in Highland would have had a better life if he had not been born. In the version of Highland in which Butt-Head had not been born, Anderson's yard is in a much better condition, Burger World has more customers and McVicker still has his hair. items.summary: Facing a shortage of criminal suspects, Lt. Dangle declares a zero-tolerance policy, only to find himself becoming the first criminal when he rear-ends a civilian's car. Fortunately, he discovers evidence of a crime in the car's trunk.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Reno 911!/Reno.911.S01.DVDRip.XviD-Fov/Reno 911! - S01E02 - Fireworks.avi
items.summary: Suspected Fireworks possession Jones and Garcia go to talk to a guy named Carl about illegal fireworks. Prostitution sting Weigel goes undercover and dresses up as prostitute with no results. A.P.B robbery in progress Jones and Garcia make Jehovah witnesses get down on the ground. The deputies mess around with the fireworks they get where Dangle accidentally sets off one in the van which lights up all the fireworks which go of in the van.
items.title: Fireworks

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Reno 911!/Reno.911.S01.DVDRip.XviD-Fov/Reno 911! - S01E03 - Execution Tickets.avi
items.summary:
Dangle and Junior try to win tickets to the Amy Grant concert off the radio by naming every Stephen Sondheim musical when they accidentally hit the back of a car (I know, Dangle seems to do that every episode.)  At the morning roll call, Dangle announces that he has two passes to a public execution.  The officers in the department have to be on the lookout for perps with specific features in a weird scavenger hunt.  It concentrates for the rest of the episode the various ways the officers attempt to manipulate the hunt.

Garcia ends up winning by bringing in an over 6'5"" Jewish crack head with a wig and a tattoo of a bird (being Jewish was double the points.)  He takes the hooker that Williams had arrested to the execution, and all the other officers flip him off as he leaves.
items.title: Execution Tickets

items.summary:
In a short resolution to season three's cliffhangers, it turns out that Garcia and Dangle are pulled out of the car safe (and naked), and, unfortunately, the call placed to the prison was a wrong number, so Craig is killed.

Six months later, Wiegel comes back from her "personal leave" pregnant. It turns out that it was not Craig that impregnated her, but rather via a sperm bank that Junior and Dangle may or may not have contributed to.

Also, Carrot Top goes insane in a Harrah's hotel, throwing furniture out of the presidential suite, shooting at people and stealing police cars.
items.title: Wiegel's Pregnant

items.summary: Jerry is ecstatic that a woman he met on the road is coming to stay with him in New York. George and Kramer weigh in on how Jerry should best approach the situation.
items.title: The Seinfeld Chronicles

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S01 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S01E02 The Robbery [R].mp4
items.summary: Jerry meets an attractive woman at a party but by the time she leaves, he has only learned where she works. Jerry stakes out the mystery woman's office with George so that he can â€œcasuallyâ€ bump into her.
items.title: The Stake Out

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S01 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S01E03 Male Unbonding [R].mp4
items.summary: Jerry is robbed after Kramer fails to close the apartment door. Elaine talks Jerry into looking at a fabulous apartment in the hopes that she can then have Jerryâ€™s place. Things are further complicated when George decides he wants the new place too.
items.title: The Robbery

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S01 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S01E04 The Stock Tip [R].mp4
items.summary: Jerry tries to â€œbreak-upâ€ with his obnoxious childhood friend but his pathetic weeping leads Jerry to give him another chance. Elaine helps Jerry come up with excuses to avoid him.
items.title: Male Unbonding

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E01 The Ex-Girlfriend [R].mp4
items.summary: George has doubts about his current relationship that he broke off. Elaine is curious about a relationship that she has with a guy in her building that has degenerated over the past two years. Jerry is reluctantly drawn into George's ex-relationship when he picks up some books left at her apartment. Although he wants to break it off with her, she has this "psycho-sexual" hold over him and he becomes worried about what George might think if he lets this relationship develop. Elaine confronts the guy in her building and Jerry's relationship maybe in jeopardy when his girlfriend sees his act.
items.title: The Ex-Girlfriend

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E02 The Pony Remark [R].mp4
items.summary: Jerry's parents come to town for a 50th anniversary party. Jerry bets Kramer that he won't complete his plans to renovate his apartment with levels in a month. Jerry takes Elaine to the dinner and he makes an observation about children who have ponies, this remark offends the guest of honor. When she dies soon afterwards, Jerry wonders if he should go to the funeral or go to his championship softball game. Elaine wonders about the fate of the apartment, when she hears the widower is moving to Arizona. George wonders if it will ever be possible for him to have sex again.
items.title: The Pony Remark

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E03 The Jacket [R].mp4
items.summary: Jerry buys a real expensive new suede jacket with a colorful inner lining. George has a song from Les Miserables that he just can't get out of his mind. Kramer is supposed pickup a magician friend's doves, and needs someone to help him for two minutes; Elaine takes on the job. Kramer promises she'll get "a lift" to the hotel where Jerry and George are meeting her and her father, Alton Benes, an author cut from Hemingway cloth. Jerry and George suffer while waiting with Elaine's father. When it begins to snow, Jerry turns his new jacket inside out, to protect it, but Alton Benes doesn't want to be seen on the street with him.
items.title: The Jacket

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E04 The Phone Message [R].mp4
items.summary: George blows an invitation upstairs with his latest girlfriend and then when he tries to make restitution he leaves progressively nastier messages on her answering machine. He gets the chance to prevent her from hearing her messages by having Jerry switch the tape out of her machine, while he distracts her. Jerry and his girlfriend have a disagreement about a TV commercial for Dockers, and his telling his friends about their conflict.
items.title: The Phone Message

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E05 The Apartment [R].mp4
items.summary: Kramer tries mousse in his hair. Jerry gets Elaine an opportunity to get the apartment right above him, before he realizes the possible implications. George tests the "man with a wedding band" theory of meeting women.
items.title: The Apartment

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E06 The Statue [R].mp4
items.summary: Jerry has a box of stuff his grandfather left him. Inside is an interesting looking statue that could replace one George's parents had years ago, but he broke. George plans to pick the statue up later but in the meantime he tells his parents about the replacement statue. Meanwhile the boyfriend of a bitter Finnish author (whose latest work Elaine is going to edit) is going to clean Jerry's apartment. When Jerry returns to his apartment it is cleaned beyond reason. Later when Jerry and Elaine are at the author's apartment, they see the statue on her mantelpiece. Getting it back may jeopardize Elaine's chance at being an editor, but save George from his parent's wrath.
items.title: The Statue

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E07 The Revenge [R].mp4
items.summary: George quits his job in a huff after he is demoted to using the regular bathroom. Newman tells Kramer that he plans to jump off the building. Jerry suggests that George just go back into work next Monday morning and pretend like nothing happened; however, that doesn't work. Newman jumps, from the second floor. George plots revenge, and with Elaine's help, tries to slip his boss "a Mickey." Jerry suspects that his launderer is a larcenist after he discovers that $1500 he had stashed in his laundry bag is missing. Kramer helps Jerry get revenge by bringing a bag of concrete in to put into one of the wash machines.
items.title: The Revenge

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E08 The Heart Attack [R].mp4
items.summary: George thinks he's had a heart attack. The doctor tells him otherwise, but he might want to get his tonsils and adenoids removed. Elaine is interested in the doctor and he is interested in her tongue. George not wanting to deal with the cost, follows Kramer's suggestion of going to a holistic healer. The healer's cure turns George purple and the ride to the hospital is delayed over a Chuckle.
items.title: The Heart Attack

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E09 The Deal [R].mp4
items.summary: Jerry and Elaine are watching TV late at night and stumble across "naked people" and that gets them both discussing whether they could have a relationship and not jeopardize their friendship. George says it can't be done, but Jerry and Elaine devise "a system"; however, it develops a little trouble when her birthday comes along.
items.title: The Deal

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E10 The Baby Shower [R].mp4
items.summary: Elaine needs to use Jerry's apartment to hold a baby shower for a woman that once dated George. George reflects that she was "unequivocally the worst date of my life." Jerry has to go out of town for a show, so he lets Elaine use the apartment. Kramer sells Jerry on the idea on getting an illegal cable hookup. The party begins. The cable guys come to install the hookup. Jerry's show gets canceled, so he returns to the apartment with George (who's prepared to confront the bad date). Jerry is the victim of his own confrontation.
items.title: The Baby Shower

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E11 The Chinese Restaurant [R].mp4
items.summary: Jerry, Elaine and George stop for a quick Chinese dinner before a showing of Plan 9 From Outer Space on the big screen. However, while waiting a really long time to get a table, Jerry sees a woman whose name he can't recall; George needs to use a phone he can't have and Elaine needs food, more than those seated ahead of them.
items.title: The Chinese Restaurant

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S02 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S02E12 The Busboy [R].mp4
items.summary: George inadvertently meddles in the life of a busboy, by getting him fired. He tries to rectify things; however, he winds up compounding them by losing the busboy's cat. Elaine discovers that a week is much too long to have a houseguest. She does everything in her power to get him out. The busboy's life is saved and made for the better after his involvement with George, until he meets Elaine's houseguest.
items.title: The Busboy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S03 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S03E01 The Note [R].mp4
items.summary: Physical therapy proves painful as Jerry has a misunderstanding with his therapist; and he finds a way for insurance to cover treatment for Elaine and a paranoid George.
items.title: The Note

items.summary: George's relationship with a former IRS worker eases Jerry's tax worries--until she becomes George's former relationship; Kramer sees too much of Elaine while seeing her roommate.
items.title: The Truth

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S03 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S03E10 The Stranded [R].mp4

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Seinfeld/Seinfeld S03 [Remastered] (360p)/Seinfeld S03E12 The Red Dot [R].mp4
