items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E01. Simpsons Roasting on an Open Fire.mp4
items.summary: Homer's Christmas bonus is canceled and the rainy-day funds are needed to pay for Bart's tattoo removal.
items.title: Simpsons Roasting on an Open Fire
items.titleSort: Simpsons Roasting on an Open Fire

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E02. Bart the Genius.mp4
items.summary: Bart is fearing that he will fail an intelligence test, Bart switches exams with Martin Prince. When school psychologist Dr. Pryor studies the results, he thinks that Bart is a genius, and Bart is enrolled into a new school for genius kids. Bart doesn't fit in very well though.
items.title: Bart the Genius

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E03. Homer's Odyssey.mp4
items.summary: Bart's class is on a field trip in the nuclear power plant in Springfield, where his father Homer works. When he breaks a pipe in the building, he is fired from his job, making him miserable. Homer is suddenly desperate for money and steals Bart's piggy bank for money, but all there is are a few cents. Homer feels guilty and he has the thought to threaten to kill himself. But Homer's family stops him and they tell him how much they love him.
items.title: Homer's Odyssey

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E04. There's No Disgrace Like Home.mp4
items.summary: When the Simpsons go to Mr. Burns mansion for a party, Homer looks at all the families that are happy and spend time together. Homer becomes embarrassed that his family isn't as happy as other families, so he finds ways to make his family happier. He eventually finds a family therapist that makes families get along. But it's hard to get the Simpsons to make a family as one.
items.title: There's No Disgrace Like Home

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E05. Bart the General.mp4
items.summary: Terrorized by the school bully, Bart seeks counsel from Grandpa Simpson, who takes him to a warfare expert for basic training.
items.title: Bart the General

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E06. Moaning Lisa.mp4
items.summary: Lisa is sent home from school with a note exempting her from games because she is sad, though she perks up when she meets fellow saxophonist Bleeding Gums Murphy and Marge encourages her to express her moods. Homer, meanwhile, sick of always beaten by his son at video games, finds a boy who can teach him to win but, just as he is about to triumph, Marge unplugs the television leaving Bart's victories unchallenged.
items.title: Moaning Lisa

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E07. Call of the Simpsons.mp4
items.summary: The Simpsons put the wild back in the wilderness when their RV goes over a cliff and Homer and Bart go for help, get lost and lose their clothes.
items.title: The Call of the Simpsons

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E08. The Tell-Tale Head.mp4
items.summary: Homer and Bart are being pursued by an angry mob through the streets of Springfield, baying for their blood. It turns out that Bart, hoping to impress the town bullies, sawed the head of the statue of town founder Jedediah Springfield. But when he discovered how appalled they were to find the head gone, enlisted Homer's help in replacing it. After he apologizes to the crowd, they forgive him.
items.title: The Telltale Head

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E09.  Jacques To Be Wild (aka Life on the Fast Lane).mp4
items.summary: Homer's bowling-ball gift "for Marge" prompts her to take up the sport--and maybe also a handsome instructor who offers to teach her "many things."
items.title: Life on the Fast Lane

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E10. Homer's Night Out.mp4
items.summary: Shutterbug Bart captures Homer with a sexy entertainer at a bachelor party.
items.title: Homer's Night Out

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E11. The Crepes of Wrath.mp4
items.summary: Bart flushes a cherry bomb at school, nearly injuring Principal Skinner's mother, Agnes, in the process. An exasperated Skinner tells Homer and Marge that since expulsion would not do Bart any good, he's placing him in a foreign-exchange student program. Bart is sent to France, where his host family are unethical winemakers who plan to employ him as a slave.
items.title: The Crepes of Wrath

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E12. Krusty Gets Busted.mp4
items.summary: Bart's TV hero Krusty the Clown is arrested for a convenience-store robbery, and witness Homer must testify against the clown.
items.title: Krusty Gets Busted

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 01/S01E13. Some Enchanted Evening.mp4
items.summary: Marge and Homer want to have a second honeymoon at a hotel but,due to Bart's naughtiness, have trouble in finding a baby-sitter, until the stern-looking Ms. Botz arrives. In fact, she is the notorious Baby-Sitter Bandit who robs the houses in her care but the kids manage to overpower her - although an unaware Homer releases her again, and she escapes, leaving the news channel to label him a local boob.
items.title: Some Enchanted Evening

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E01. Bart Gets An F.mp4
items.summary: Bart disappoints Marge yet again by his appalling history grades and the school psychiatrist reckons that unless he shapes up, he must sit the fourth grade again next year. But if he can successfully pass the history paper one last time he will be clear. Since Martin refuses to help, Bart prays for a miracle - which comes in the form of a snow storm which closes the school and gives him extra revision time.
items.title: Bart Gets an 'F'

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E02. Simpson and Delilah.mp4
items.summary: Homer uses his medical insurance to buy Dimoxinil, a miracle hair-growth formula. After growing luxurious locks, he's given a promotion which allows him to hire a secretary named Karl and makes grand promises to his family at home.
items.title: Simpson and Delilah

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E03. Treehouse of Horror.mp4
items.summary: The Simpson kids hide in the family treehouse and tell each other spooky stories. The first regards haunted houses, the second introduces Kang and Kodos for the first time in an alien abduction, and the third is a Simpson-adapted retelling of The Raven.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E04. 2 Cars in Every Garage, 3 Eyes on Every Fish.mp4
items.summary: Bart catches a three-eyed fish in the river near Springfield Nuclear Power Plant. When the fish story is featured prominently in the local news, the plant is inspected and then fined millions of dollars for its many safety violations. Infuriated, Mr. Burns decides to run for governor so he can do away with the regulations that are costing him so much money.
items.title: Two Cars in Every Garage and Three Eyes on Every Fish
items.titleSort: Two Cars in Every Garage and Three Eyes on Every Fish

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E05. Dancin' Homer.mp4
items.summary: Homer fires up the crowd at a Springfield Isotopes baseball game and is chosen to be the team's new mascot. He immediately becomes a popular attraction and the Isotopes start a winning streak. As a result, Homer is promoted to a team in Capital City, the Capital City Capitals.
items.title: Dancin' Homer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E06. Dead Putting Society.mp4
items.summary: Bart and Todd Flanders decide to enter a miniature golf tournament. Homer becomes confident that Bart will win and makes a bet with Ned that the father of the boy that does not win will have to mow their neighbors lawn in their wife's Sunday dress.
items.title: Dead Putting Society

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E07. Bart vs. Thanksgiving.mp4
items.summary: Lisa makes a table centerpiece for the Thanksgiving dinner, which Bart accidentally destroys. After he is sent to his room by his parents, Bart angrily runs away from home and experiences a very different kind of Thanksgiving holiday.
items.title: Bart vs. Thanksgiving

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E08. Bart the Daredevil.mp4
items.summary: The Simpsons go to a Monster truck rally that features famous daredevil Lance Murdock. Bart immediately becomes enamored and decides that he wants to become a daredevil as well. His first stunt ends in injury, but to gain the respect of his friends, he promises a far more impressive feat to them: to jump the Springfield Gorge.
items.title: Bart the Daredevil

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E09. Itchy & Scratchy & Marge.mp4
items.summary: When Maggie attacks her father,Psycho-style with a mallet,Marge blames the violent TV cartoon series 'Itchy and Scratchy' and gets it banned. Children,released from the spell of constant television viewing,learn to play outdoors again. However when Marge refuses to condemn Michelangelo's David as obscene she is branded a hypocrite and the cartoon is restored.
items.title: Itchy & Scratchy & Marge

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E10. Bart Gets Hit By A Car.mp4
items.summary: After Mr. Burns hits Bart with his car, ambulance-chasing attorney Lionel Hutz persuades Homer and Marge to sue for a million dollars.
items.title: Bart Gets Hit by a Car
items.titleSort: Bart Gets Hit by a Car

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E11. One Fish, Two Fish, Blowfish, Blue Fish.mp4
items.summary: After the family have visited the Happy Sumo sushi restaurant, Homer is led to believe that he has eaten a poisonous fugu fish and will be dead by the next day. He therefore makes a list of all the things he must do such as making his peace with his father and insulting Burns,which gets him sacked. Preparing to die, he falls asleep listening to a tape of Larry King reading the Bible but next morning wakes up to find he was not poisoned after all.
items.title: One Fish, Two Fish, Blowfish, Blue Fish
items.titleSort: One Fish, Two Fish, Blowfish, Blue Fish

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E12. The Way We Was.mp4
items.summary: Marge and Homer tell the children how they first met - as high school students in 1974. Homer tried to impress Marge by pretending to be a French student to take her to the prom but she chose Artie Zif as her escort instead. However after Artie has made a nuisance of himself Marge rejects him and returns to the man she will marry.
items.title: The Way We Was

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E13. Homer vs. Lisa and the Eighth Commandment.mp4
items.summary: Lisa is shocked when Homer does an under the counter deal with a television installation engineer and gets cable T.V. for free as it is against the eighth commandment - Thou Shalt Not Steal. Lisa and Homer both,unsuccessfully, try to convince each other of their point of view but,after consultation with the Reverend Lovejoy,Lisa knows exactly what she must do - pull the plug whilst everybody is watching the big fight at on Homer's television.
items.title: Homer vs. Lisa and the 8th Commandment
items.titleSort: Homer vs. Lisa and the 8th Commandment

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E14. Principal Charming.mp4
items.summary: Selma is looking for a husband and asks Marge to help her find one; Marge in turn asks Homer to help. Homer thinks that Principal Skinner is a good prospect and plans Skinner for a setup with Selma. However, when Homer arranges for them to meet, Skinner falls for Patty instead, to everyone's chagrin.
items.title: Principal Charming

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E15. Oh Brother, Where Art Thou.mp4
items.summary: Homer discovers that he has an illegitimate half-brother who is now the very successful car manufacturer Herb Powell. The Simpsons are invited to stay at Herb's mansion and, considering Homer to be an average American and typical consumer, Herb asks him to design a new car for the company. It is, however, a total disaster and results in Herb's bankruptcy.
items.title: Oh Brother, Where Art Thou?

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E16. Bart's Dog Gets An F.mp4
items.summary: After a series of destructive acts, Homer decides that Santa's Little Helper must go unless he passes obedience school. As the dog's last hours with the family approach, Bart must find a way to get through to him.
items.title: Bart's Dog Gets an 'F'

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E17. Old Money.mp4
items.summary: Grampa begins dating Bea Simmons, another resident of the Springfield Retirement Castle, but she dies. She was a very rich woman, and leaves all her money to Grampa. He is at first unsure how to spend it, and invites suggestions from all-comers who, apart from Lisa, are greedy and want it for themselves. He ultimately donates it to make much needed improvements to the retirement home, telling everybody: "Dignity's on me, friends."
items.title: Old Money

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E18. Brush with Greatness.mp4
items.summary: Marge revives her interest in art - she once did a painting of Ringo Starr - and Mr. Burns commissions her to do a portrait of him, depicting him as a beautiful man. However, after he has insulted Homer's weight the painting shows him nude, though Marge explains that she intended to show his vulnerability as a frail old man and Burns is highly impressed.
items.title: Brush with Greatness

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E19. Lisa's Substitute.mp4
items.summary: Lisa's teacher Miss Hoover becomes ill and has a substitute, Mr. Bergstrom. Lisa enjoys his teaching methods and quickly develops a crush on him. Meanwhile, Bart runs for class president against Martin Prince and proves to be a very popular candidate.
items.title: Lisa's Substitute

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E20. War of the Simpsons.mp4
items.summary: At a lakeside retreat for married couples, Marge is determined to fix her marriage with Homer, but Homer is more determined to catch General Sherman, the freakishly large catfish that lives in the lake.
items.title: The War of the Simpsons

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E21. Three Men and a Comic Book.mp4
items.summary: Bart, Milhouse, and Martin pool their money to buy the new first issue of Radioactive Man, but their investment and their friendship are threatened when they can't agree on who will keep it.
items.title: Three Men and a Comic Book
items.titleSort: Three Men and a Comic Book

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 02/S02E22. Blood Feud.mp4
items.summary: When Mr. Burns is saved by a transfusion of Bart's blood, Homer expects a handsome reward but is outraged to receive only a simple thank-you note.
items.title: Blood Feud

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E01. Stark Raving Dad.mp4
items.summary: Through a series of misunderstandings, Homer is put into a mental hospital and his roommate is a man who talks and sings like Michael Jackson. Everything is cleared up and Homer is released, and he brings "Michael Jackson" home, where nobody believes him. However, in all the confusion, everyone has forgotten about Lisa's birthday--including Bart, who didn't even remember to buy a present.
items.title: Stark Raving Dad

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E02. Mr. Lisa Goes to Washington.mp4
items.summary: Lisa wins the local competition of an essay contest, earning the family a trip to Washington, D.C. for the finals. Lisa sees Bob Arnold (her own representative) taking a bribe. Disgusted, she changes her previous uplifting essay into a cynical one denouncing corruption in government in general and Bob Arnold in particular.
items.title: Mr. Lisa Goes to Washington

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E03. When Flanders Failed.mp4
items.summary: Flanders suffers a failure after Homer wishes him ill.
items.title: When Flanders Failed

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E04. Bart the Murderer.mp4
items.summary: Bart is hired to work in a Mafia bar run by Fat Tony (making his first appearance). Bart is late for work due to having been put in detention by Principal Skinner. Fat Tony announces that he and his men will "meet and greet" Skinner, and shortly after that, Skinner disappears. Both Bart and Fat Tony are charged with Skinner's murder, and at the trial, Fat Tony tries to pin the murder (and all of his other illegal activities) on Bart.
items.title: Bart the Murderer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E05. Homer Defined.mp4
items.summary: Homer prevents a nuclear meltdown,purely by picking a button to press at random, but he is declared a hero and asked to give a talk on plant safety. During the talk he is called upon to prevent another meltdown and exposed as a lucky chancer who only averted an accident by mistake. Marge goes to see Millhouse's mother who has barred her son from seeing Bart,whom she regards as a bad influence,and persuades her to change her mind.
items.title: Homer Defined

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E06. Like Father, Like Clown.mp4
items.summary: Krusty the Clown has dinner with the Simpsons, and reveals that he is Jewish, his real name is Herschel Krustofsky, and he is estranged from his rabbi father. They parted ways over Krusty's becoming a clown instead of following his father and becoming a rabbi. Bart and Lisa see Krusty becoming depressed, and they take it upon themselves to reunite him with his father.
items.title: Like Father, Like Clown

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E07. Treehouse of Horror II.mp4
items.summary: The Simpsons go to a market sale and receive a severed monkey's paw which can grant five wishes. Bart has magic powers so he can turn people into anything he wants if they be naughty to him and he turns Homer into a Jack-in-the-box. Mr Burns' puts Homer's brain into a robot.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror II

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E08. Lisa's Pony.mp4
items.summary: Homer loses much of Lisa's respect for him after he botches the task of getting her a saxophone reed she needs for a talent show. Homer realizes that he's been ignoring Lisa since she was a baby and thinks that's what's causing problems now, so he buys Lisa a pony to change her opinion of him.
items.title: Lisa's Pony

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E09. Saturdays of Thunder.mp4
items.summary: Trying to be a better father, Homer helps Bart build a soapbox racer. Bart's racer is a flop, but Martin Prince's is the fastest and wins the race. When Martin is hurt, he asks Bart to fill in as driver so that at least one of them can beat Nelson Muntz in the race.
items.title: Saturdays of Thunder

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E10. Flaming Moe's.mp4
items.summary: Homer tells Moe the story of how he created a drink by combining several liquids (including cough syrup) and setting it on fire, which he called the "Flaming Homer." Moe serves the drink in his bar and quickly renames it the "Flaming Moe," insisting that he is the inventor rather than Homer.
items.title: Flaming Moe's

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E11. Burns Verkaufen Der Kraftwerk.mp4
items.summary: Wishing to retire and pursue other interests, Mr. Burns sells the nuclear power plant to two German businessmen. The new owners evaluate the plant and its employees with the goal of making it more efficient and decide to lay off Homer. Meanwhile, Mr. Burns finds retirement to be unsatisfying.
items.title: Burns Verkaufen der Kraftwerk

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E12. I Married Marge.mp4
items.summary: Whilst Marge seeks confirmation that she is pregnant Homer tells the children how she became pregnant with Bart - after a sex session after seeing 'The Empire Strikes Back' and they married in haste. Marge's family looked down on Homer as he could only get a succession of menial jobs but when he found work at the nuclear power plant he told them to respect him.After he has told his story Marge comes back to say she is not pregnant after all.
items.title: I Married Marge

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E13. Radio Bart.mp4
items.summary: For his birthday Bart gets a microphone which can transmit through the radio and uses it to convince Springfield that a boy called Timmy O'Toole has fallen down a well, a prank which attracts a media circus until exposed as a hoax. This means that when Bart also falls down a well people are initially reluctant to dig him out.
items.title: Radio Bart

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E14. Lisa The Greek.mp4
items.summary: Lisa's ability to pick winning football teams kicks off a strong bond with Homer.
items.title: Lisa the Greek

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E15. Homer Alone.mp4
items.summary: After a stressful day, Marge has a nervous breakdown and parks her car in the middle of a bridge. Marge decides to take a vacation by herself. Bart and Lisa are sent to stay with Patty and Selma, while Homer is left at home to take care of Maggie. When Maggie goes missing, Homer only just manages to find her before Marge gets home.
items.title: Homer Alone

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E16. Bart The Lover.mp4
items.summary: Lonely Enda Krabappel has punished Bart for one of his shenanigans again, so he decides to take revenge on her by responding to a personal ad, pretending to be a potential new boyfriend. Successfully stringing her along with corresponding love letters and setting her up for a date that goes bad, he starts to feel guilty over his actions and calls for help from his family to lift her spirits.
items.title: Bart the Lover

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E17. Homer At The Bat.mp4
items.summary: Burns hires Major League ringers for the plant softball championship.
items.title: Homer at the Bat

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E18. Separate Vocations.mp4
items.summary: After taking a career aptitude test at school, Bart is surprised to hear that "police officer" is his ideal vocation, while Lisa is devastated to be told that she is only fit to be a homemaker. Bart becomes a hall monitor, while Lisa adopts a sulky, rebellious attitude.
items.title: Separate Vocations

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E19. Dog Of Death.mp4
items.summary: Lottery fever hits Springfield, but the Simpsons are forced to forgo a lottery ticket, and many other luxuries, to pay for a life-saving operation for their dog, Santa's Little Helper. All their personal lives are affected negatively by the sacrifice, and they come to resent Santa's Little Helper. He runs away and is captured by Mr. Burns, who trains him to be a guard dog.
items.title: Dog of Death

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E20. Colonel Homer.mp4
items.summary: After yet another row with Marge, Homer goes to a bar, where he hears local waitress Lurleen Lumpkin sing and is so impressed he takes her on as his client, arranging gigs and a recording contract for her. However, when they are alone in her trailer Lurleen makes a pass at him but Homer, loyal to Marge, resists and hands over her career to another agent. Lurleen publicly celebrates Homer's fidelity in a song.
items.title: Colonel Homer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E21. Black Widower.mp4
items.summary: Marge's sister Selma has been writing to Sideshow Bob whilst he was in prison, and, on his release announces their intention to marry. Bart is appalled. Unlike everybody else he is unconvinced that Bob has changed and believes that, as Selma has come into money, he will attempt to murder her on their honeymoon. And he is right. Putting two and two together Bart works out how Bob plans to blow Selma up and manages to thwart him in time.
items.title: Black Widower

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E22. Otto Show.mp4
items.summary: Spinal Tap hits Springfield, and Otto the bus driver hits the skids after being fired, taking refuge in the Simpsons' garage.
items.title: The Otto Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E23. Bart's Friend Falls In Love.mp4
items.summary: Bart resents Milhouse's new girlfriend; Homer gets the wrong subliminal tape, which has him gaining vocabulary, not losing weight.
items.title: Bart's Friend Falls in Love

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 03/S03E24. Brother Can You Spare Two Dimes.mp4
items.summary: During a routine plant physical, it is discovered that exposure to radiation has sterilized Homer. Mr. Burns pays him off with an elaborate employee appreciation ceremony, and a monetary award. Homer's half-brother Herb Powell, now a hobo, reads about it in the paper, and decide's that Homer's wealth can fund his idea for an invention that would transform baby gibberish into intelligible English.
items.title: Brother, Can You Spare Two Dimes?
items.titleSort: Brother, Can You Spare Two Dimes?

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E01. Kamp Krusty.mp4
items.summary: Bart leads an uprising at Krusty's summer camp after he and Lisa are subjected to a Dickensian sweatshop.
items.title: Kamp Krusty

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E02. A Streetcar Named Marge.mp4
items.summary: After blowing up in Homer's face, Marge is cast as the lead in a musical production with Ned Flanders as her love interest, but the more she plays the part, the madder she gets at Homer; Maggie attempts to retrieve her pacifier from the nanny.
items.title: A Streetcar Named Marge

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E03. Homer The Heretic.mp4
items.summary: Homer decides not to attend church one Sunday and has the time of his life and vows never to return to church again, however one Sunday after falling asleep while smoking a cigar he accidentally sets fire to The Simpsons house, Flanders spots the flames and rescues him, Homer comes to his senses and turns up at church the following Sunday(asleep).
items.title: Homer the Heretic

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E04. Lisa The Beauty Queen.mp4
items.summary: Homer enters Lisa into the Little Miss Springfield Pageant to help her feel better about her looks. But when she must choose between the title and her integrity, she realizes that confidence comes from within.
items.title: Lisa the Beauty Queen

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E05. Treehouse Of Horror Iii.mp4
items.summary: In "Clown Without Pity", a Krusty the Clown doll goes berserk in the Simpson home. In "King Homer", Marge is wooed by a giant ape. And final story, In "Dial 'Z' for Zombies", Bart's attempt to bring back the family cat turns the town of Springfield into a pack of bloodthirsty zombies.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror III

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E06. Itchy & Scratchy - The Movie.mp4
items.summary: Bart is punished by being barred from the Itchy and Scratchy movie.
items.title: Itchy & Scratchy: The Movie

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E07. Marge Gets A Job.mp4
items.summary: Mr. Burns is instantly smitten when Marge takes a job at the nuclear power plant.
items.title: Marge Gets a Job

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E08. New Kid On The Block.mp4
items.summary: Bart has a crush on his new neighbor, a teenage girl who only has eyes for Jimbo Jones. Bart sets out to prove that Jimbo is not as tough as he seems.
items.title: New Kid on the Block

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E09. Mr. Plow.mp4
items.summary: Homer buys a truck with an attached snow plow after he destroys his car, and to pay for it, he starts a snow shoveling business, calling himself Mr. Plow. It all goes off without a hitch, until he finds himself in competition with The Plow King, a.k.a. Barney Gumbel. Now begins the winter of discontent.
items.title: Mr. Plow

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E10. Lisa's First Word.mp4
items.summary: While trying to get Maggie to say her first word, Marge and Homer reminisce about Bart's and Lisa's first words.
items.title: Lisa's First Word

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E11. Homer's Triple Bypass.mp4
items.summary: Homer sees a discount doctor for a coronary bypass.
items.title: Homer's Triple Bypass

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E12. Marge Vs. The Monorail.mp4
items.summary: After receiving a considerable donation of money, Springfield builds a monorail system with Homer as the conductor, unaware they've just boarded a one-way train to Hell.
items.title: Marge vs. the Monorail

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E13. Selma's Choice.mp4
items.summary: After seeing Aunt Gladys die alone, Aunt Selma wants to get married and have a baby... until she spends a day babysitting Bart and Lisa at Duff Gardens.
items.title: Selma's Choice

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E14. Brother From The Same Planet.mp4
items.summary: After Homer forgets to pick up Bart from soccer practice, Bart joins a mentor program called Big Brothers presenting himself as an orphan, and is assigned a big brother called Tom. When Homer finds out, he joins the program too as a big brother.
items.title: Brother from the Same Planet

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E15. I Love Lisa.mp4
items.summary: Feeling sorry for Ralph, Lisa sends him a Valentine card. Having developed a crush on her, Ralph invites Lisa to go see the Krusty the Clown show. She accepts but after Krusty asks them if they are boyfriend and girlfriend, Lisa lets Ralph know that she just wants them to be friends.
items.title: I Love Lisa

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E16. Duffless.mp4
items.summary: After a DUI, Homer swears off beer for a month. Meanwhile, Bart and Lisa's sibling rivalry plays out in the school science fair.
items.title: Duffless

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E17. Last Exit To Springfield.mp4
items.summary: Mr. Burns revokes the dental plan from the power plant's union contract, and when Homer realizes that he'll now have to pay for Lisa's new braces, he leads the power plant employees on a strike, while Mr. Burns struggles to put an end to the rioting.
items.title: Last Exit to Springfield

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E18. So It's Come To This A Simpsons Clip Show.mp4
items.summary: An April Fools' Day prank provides the jumping-off point for Simpson family flashbacks.
items.title: So It's Come to This: A Simpsons Clip Show
items.titleSort: So It's Come to This: A Simpsons Clip Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E19. The Front.mp4
items.summary: After watching a particularly tame Itchy and Scratchy show Lisa and Bart send one of their own scripts to the studio but it is rejected as they under age so they write some more and get Grandpa to say that he is the author. As a result Grandpa wins an award but at the presentation ceremony is horrified to see one of the cartoons for the first time. Homer,meanwhile,has to attend night school after it is discovered that he never actually graduated.
items.title: The Front

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E20. Whacking Day.mp4
items.summary: Marge teaches Bart at home after Skinner expels him. Lisa is horrified to find that it is Whacking Day,when Springfield citizens beat snakes to death so,helped by Barry White,she and Bart rescue the snakes by directing them to the Simpsons' house. Bart discovers that the real origin of Whacking Day was to beat up Irishman,a fact which impresses Skinner who lets him back in the school.
items.title: Whacking Day

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E21. Marge In Chains.mp4
items.summary: Overwhelmed by her family's demands during a flu epidemic, Marge accidentally shoplifts at the Kwik-E-Mart and winds up in prison.
items.title: Marge in Chains

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 04/S04E22. Krusty Gets Kancelled.mp4
items.summary: Krusty's Hollywood pals help when his show is canceled after a new star causes his ratings to plummet.
items.title: Krusty Gets Kancelled

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E01. Homer's Barbershop Quartet.mp4
items.summary: Homer recalls when he, Apu, Barney and Principal Skinner became recording icons.
items.title: Homer's Barbershop Quartet

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E02. Cape Feare.mp4
items.summary: An anonymous letter writer makes ominous threats to Bart. The Simpsons discover they were sent by Sideshow Bob who, when released from prison, harasses the Simpsons and then attempts to kill Bart with a machete. But Bob's vanity foils him yet again.
items.title: Cape Feare

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E03. Homer Goes To College.mp4
items.summary: Homer takes Nuclear Physics 101 at the local college, where he gets a trio of nerdy tutors expelled for extracurricular activities.
items.title: Homer Goes to College

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E04. Rosebud.mp4
items.summary: Burns' birthday is approaching and he longs for Bobo,the teddy bear he had as a child. Bobo has had an illustrious history,including flying the Atlantic with Lindbergh and being buried in Arctic ice,some of which is sold as ice cubes to the Simpsons so that Bobo is now Maggie's toy. Burns attempts theft,bribery and robbery to get his Bobo back but the family stand firm against him until finally Maggie,feeling sorry for him,offers him Bobo.
items.title: Rosebud

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E05. Treehouse Of Horror Iv.mp4
items.summary: Homer, after seeing no more donuts in the power plant, says he would sell his soul for a donut, for the devil appears to be Ned Flanders. Whilst riding to school, Bart sees a gremlins on the side of the bus which only he can see. The Simpsons family go to Mr Burns' haunted castle where they think that Mr Burns is Count Dracula.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror IV

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E06. Marge On The Lam.mp4
items.summary: Marge starts hanging out with Ruth Powers from next door,to the annoyance of Homer,who feels neglected. When Chief Wiggum tries to flag the women down in Ruth's car Ruth keeps going,saying that she has stolen the car from her ex-husband. A high speed chase follows in the manner of 'Thelma and Louise',culminating at the top of a canyon,where the women manage to stop in time but Wiggum,with Homer as his passenger,goes flying into the void.
items.title: Marge on the Lam

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E07. Bart's Inner Child.mp4
items.summary: Springfield emulates Bart after he's praised by a self-help guru.
items.title: Bart's Inner Child

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E08. Boy-scoutz 'n The Hood.mp4
items.summary: After a reckless Squishee bender with Milhouse, Bart wakes to the shocking realization that he joined the Junior Campers. Lured by pocketknives and knot-tying lessons, Bart assimilates into the group but then must face the father-son rafting trip.
items.title: Boy-Scoutz 'N the Hood

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E09. The Last Temptation Of Homer.mp4
items.summary: Homer struggles with his attraction to new coworker Mindy, a beautiful engineer whose love for doughnuts is equal to his own.
items.title: The Last Temptation of Homer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E10. Springfield (or, How I Learned To Stop Worrying And Love Legalized Gambling).mp4
items.summary: Legalized gambling comes to Springfield, and Marge becomes addicted; Robert Goulet entertains at Bart's casino for kids.
items.title: $pringfield

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E11. Homer The Vigilante.mp4
items.summary: Homer leads a vigilante group to catch the Springfield Cat Burglar, who then robs the museum.
items.title: Homer the Vigilante

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E12. Bart Gets Famous.mp4
items.summary: When an on-air remark catapults Bart to instant stardom, he finds that fame isn't all it's cracked up to be.
items.title: Bart Gets Famous

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E13. Homer And Apu.mp4
items.summary: Homer participates in a hidden camera investigation of unsanitary food preparation at the Kwik-E-Mart, which costs Apu his job. Apu then enlists Homer's help on a journey to India to get his job back, while James Woods becomes the new Kwik-E-Mart clerk, as part of his research for a film project.
items.title: Homer and Apu

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E14. Lisa Vs. Malibu Stacy.mp4
items.summary: Lisa's outrage over the gender stereotypes reinforced by a new talking doll prompts her to confront the dollmaker.
items.title: Lisa vs. Malibu Stacy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E15. Deep Space Homer.mp4
items.summary: The powers that be at NASA, distraught over low television ratings for their space launches, decide to improve them by putting a private citizen on their next space shuttle. After receiving an angry phone call from Homer, they decide he is their man.
items.title: Deep Space Homer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E16. Homer Loves Flanders.mp4
items.summary: Flanders' extra ticket to the big game makes him Homer's new best friend, a role that sorely tests Flanders' patience.
items.title: Homer Loves Flanders

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E17. Bart Gets An Elephant.mp4
items.summary: After winning a phone-in competition Bart has a choice of prize of either $10,000 or an elephant, he chooses the latter, naming him Stampy. The Simpsons are in chaos after Stampy wrecks the house and eats all the food. They have no alternative, Stampy must go to an animal refuge.
items.title: Bart Gets an Elephant

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E18. Burns' Heir.mp4
items.summary: Bart is picked to be Burns' heir and moves into the Burns mansion, prompting Homer and Marge to hire a deprogrammer to get him back.
items.title: Burns' Heir

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E19. Sweet Seymour Skinner's Baadasssss Song.mp4
items.summary: Bart takes his dog to school, which gets Skinner fired, which in turn leaves Bart missing his archnemesis.
items.title: Sweet Seymour Skinner's Baadasssss Song

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E20. The Boy Who Knew Too Much.mp4
items.summary: After playing hooky from school, Bart sneaks in to Mayor Quimby's nephew Freddy's birthday party and witnesses a confrontation between Freddy and a waiter, Freddy is accused of beating the waiter but Bart knows what really happened, should he keep quiet or tell the truth and risk getting Cort playing hooky?
items.title: The Boy Who Knew Too Much

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E21. Lady Bouvier's Lover.mp4
items.summary: Marge arranges for her mother Jacqueline Bouvier to start dating Grandpa Simpson and all is going well until Burns cuts in and takes her away from Grandpa Abe. When he hears that she is getting married to Burns he goes to the church and,in a nod to the climax of the film 'The Graduate',runs away with her and,after she has declared that she doesn't want to marry either of them,they get on a bus together.
items.title: Lady Bouvier's Lover

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 05/S05E22. Secrets Of A Successful Marriage.mp4
items.summary: Homer teaches a class on marriage, but sharing secrets about his own union gets him kicked out of the house.
items.title: Secrets of a Successful Marriage

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E01. Bart Of Darkness.mp4
items.summary: In a Rear Window parody, the Simpsons buy a swimming pool and everybody in the neighborhood joins in the enjoyment--except for Bart, whose broken leg prevents him from swimming. He soon becomes obsessed with looking through his telescope and even suspects Ned Flanders of murdering his wife.
items.title: Bart of Darkness

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E02. Lisa's Rival.mp4
items.summary: Lisa feels threatened when a new girl moves to Springfield: Allison is smart, pretty, a great saxophone player and a crack diorama builder. Lisa tries to befriend her new rival, but she's consumed with envy and competitiveness.
items.title: Lisa's Rival

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E03. Another Simpsons Clip Show.mp4
items.summary: After reading the weepy best-seller The Bridges of Madison County, Marge sits down with the family and recalls romantic moments, along with temptations from her bowling instructor Jacques and Homer's coworker Mindy.
items.title: Another Simpsons Clip Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E04. Itchy & Scratchy Land.mp4
items.summary: The Simpsons go to Itchy and Scratchyland,a theme park based on the violent television cartoon, where Bart and Homer are both arrested for annoying actors dressed as Itchy. However when the robot characters turn violent in the manner of 'Westworld' and the staff evacuate,the Simpsons are the heroes of the day by defeating the robots by using camera flash bulbs.
items.title: Itchy & Scratchy Land

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E05. Sideshow Bob Roberts.mp4
items.summary: Sideshow Bob is released from prison, runs for mayor as a Republican, and defeats "Diamond" Joe Quimby in the election. But a "Deep-Throat"-type informant tells Bart and Lisa that he was fraudulently elected. It's up to them to find the evidence.
items.title: Sideshow Bob Roberts

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E06. Treehouse Of Horror V.mp4
items.summary: The Simpsons get hired by Mr Burns to take care of his country-side mansion for the winter where Homer starts going mad. In the second segment, Homer's toaster breaks and in trying to fix it, he inadvertently made it into a time-machine in which cause terrible consequences. In the third segment, Bart and Lisa's teachers start killing and eating the students in the school when they misbehave.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror V

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E07. Bart's Girlfriend.mp4
items.summary: Bart falls for Reverand Lovejoy's beautiful, yet manipulative, daughter Jessica Lovejoy who has a way of making boys do whatever she wants them to do but when but when Bart is accused by the whole town of stealing money from the church collection plate Lisa springs into action to find the real thief and all fingers point to Ms Lovejoy. Meryl Streep guest voices.
items.title: Bart's Girlfriend

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E08. Lisa On Ice.mp4
items.summary: Lisa's surprising ability at hockey spawns jealousy in Bart and a showdown when their teams meet.
items.title: Lisa on Ice

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E09. Homer Bad Man.mp4
items.summary: When Homer gropes for a gummy candy stuck to the babysitter's pants, she mistakes his intentions and turns the town against him.
items.title: Homer Badman

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E10. Grandpa Vs. Sexual Inadequacy.mp4
items.summary: Grampa invents an aphrodisiac tonic,which kick-starts the sex lives of most of the adults in Springfield and he and Homer go on the road to sell it. However at an old farm-house where the Simpsons once lived,Grampa reveals to Homer that his birth was accidental. Homer is angry and the two part. But after reflection,they reconcile back at the farm-house but also manage to burn it down.
items.title: Grampa vs. Sexual Inadequacy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E11. Fear Of Flying.mp4
items.summary: When they try to go on vacation, the family discovers Marge's debilitating fear of flying. Marge consults a psychoanalyst to find the source of her baffling fear.
items.title: Fear of Flying

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E12. Homer The Great.mp4
items.summary: Homer secretly trails Lenny and Carl to the venue of a masonic society called the Stonecutters,who enjoy elite privileges and seem to number every male in Springfield except him. When a birthmark on him shaped like the secret sign of the Stonecutters is revealed he is declared their new leader but,unhappy at the premise of having to obey him,the lodge found another society - called No Homers.
items.title: Homer the Great

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E13. And Maggie Makes Three.mp4
items.summary: The story of Maggie's birth is told in flashbacks: after Homer quits the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant to pursue his dream of working at a bowling alley, Marge reveals that she is pregnant.
items.title: And Maggie Makes Three

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E14. Bart's Comet.mp4
items.summary: When Bart is forced to assist Principal Skinner in early-morning astronomy observations, he discovers a giant comet heading towards Springfield. Facing impending doom, the entire town shows up at the Flanders family bomb shelter.
items.title: Bart's Comet

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E15. Homie The Clown.mp4
items.summary: Krusty the Clown's reckless spending forces him to open a clown college to keep afloat. New graduate Homer discovers the perks and perils of being Krusty.
items.title: Homie the Clown

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E16. Bart Vs. Australia.mp4
items.summary: Lisa tells Bart that toilet water swirls in the opposite direction in the Southern Hemisphere. Determined to find out if this is true, Bart makes a collect call to Australia. When the father of the boy he called finds out about the charges, it sparks an international incident. The Simpsons must travel to Australia to repair relations with the United States.
items.title: Bart vs. Australia

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E17. Homer Vs. Patty And Selma.mp4
items.summary: A loan from Patty and Selma makes Homer their slave; Bart is forced to take ballet.
items.title: Homer vs. Patty and Selma

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E18. A Star Is Burns.mp4
items.summary: It is decided that a film festival should be held to put Springfield on the map and cinema critic Jay Sherman comes to town and stays with the Simpsons. Various people submit films that they have made to win the critics' prize, from Burns' blockbuster presenting him as an epic hero to Barney's strangely poetic monochrome short, but the most popular choice seems to be George C. Scott in 'Man Getting Hit With a Football'.
items.title: A Star Is Burns

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E19. Lisa's Wedding.mp4
items.summary: A fortuneteller predicts Lisa's engagement and wedding to a fellow student from an upper-crust British family.
items.title: Lisa's Wedding

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E20. Two Dozen And One Greyhounds.mp4
items.summary: Santa's Little Helper and his mate She's the Fastest have twenty-five puppies but they are unhappy to be separated for sale so Burns bids for all of them and when the family refuses, sensing evil intentions, he steals them to kill and make a coat for himself. He even sings a song 'See My Vest' to celebrate the fact. However Bart and Lisa rescue the puppies and eventually Burns buys them to breed for racing.
items.title: Two Dozen and One Greyhounds

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E21. The Pta Disbands.mp4
items.summary: Due to Skinner's penny-pinching Mrs. Krabappel calls the teachers on strike. As a consequence the parents become substitute teachers but Bart feels so embarrassed by Marge teaching him that he eventually tricks Seymour and Edna into negotiation by locking them into a room together. The problem is solved by renting room space to the local prison.
items.title: The PTA Disbands

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E22. Round Springfield.mp4
items.summary: When Bart swallows a hazardous prize from a cereal box and winds up in the hospital, Lisa finds out her jazz idol Bleeding Gums Murphy has a room of his own there. Sadly, this turns out to be his deathbed, and not only is she upset about him dying, but she realizes that nobody will ever remember him for his music, unless she does something about it.
items.title: Round Springfield

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E23. The Springfield Connection.mp4
items.summary: Having foiled an attempt by ex-convict Snake to rob the family one night Marge joins the local police force and becomes extremely zealous,dishing out punishments to the family and breaking up Homer's illegal gambling school. When Homer's friend Herman gets him involved in a scam to sell stolen jeans Marge tries to arrest him but gets no help from Wiggum and eventually resigns,complaining of police corruption.
items.title: The Springfield Connection

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E24. Lemon Of Troy.mp4
items.summary: Springfield boys try to recapture the town's beloved lemon tree after it's stolen.
items.title: Lemon of Troy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 06/S06E25. Who Shot Mr. Burns (part One).mp4
items.summary: After he stole the oil underneath Springfield Elementary and blocked out the sun, the people of Springfield become fed up with Mr. Burns. The wily old miser has taken to carrying around a gun with him. The other town residents have guns, too. One fateful night, Marge finds Mr. Burns shot. Who did it? Homer? Grandpa? Barney? Moe? Skinner? Smithers? Snake? Dr. Hibbert? Bumblebee Man?
items.title: Who Shot Mr. Burns? (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E01. Who Shot Mr. Burns (part Two).mp4
items.summary: With Mr. Burns shot, Chief Wiggum investigates the crime, and nearly everyone in town has a motive. At the end, it all comes down to the Simpson DNA.
items.title: Who Shot Mr. Burns? (2)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E02. Radioactive Man.mp4
items.summary: Action hero Rainier Wolfcastle is to play Radioactive Man in a blockbuster adventure movie to be filmed in Springfield. Bart auditions to play his sidekick Fall-Out Boy but is told he is too short and the part goes to Milhouse,causing friction among the boys. Milhouse is a reluctant actor and,despite encouragement from Mickey Rooney,walks out of the picture,which is shelved as a result but Bart gets his friend back.
items.title: Radioactive Man

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E03. Home Sweet Homediddly-dum-doodily.mp4
items.summary: When Homer and Marge are found to be unfit parents, the kids are placed with the Flanders family. Reluctant participants in the Flanderses' wholesome family activities, Bart and Lisa become the targets of an emergency baptism.
items.title: Home Sweet Homediddly-Dum-Doodily

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E04. Bart Sells His Soul.mp4
items.summary: Bart sells his soul to Milhouse for five dollars, but soon regrets his decision. Meanwhile, Moe turns the Tavern into a family-friendly restaurant.
items.title: Bart Sells His Soul

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E05. Lisa The Vegetarian.mp4
items.summary: Having befriended a lamb on a trip to a petting zoo,Lisa refuses to eat a lamb chop,seeing it as a living creature,and becomes a vegetarian,ruining Homer's hog-roast barbecue. Feeling depressed she runs into Apu who introduces her to Linda and Paul McCartney,from whom she learns that it is possible to have principles but still understand others' view points.
items.title: Lisa the Vegetarian

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E06. Treehouse Of Horror Vi.mp4
items.summary: In "Attack of the 50 Foot Eyesores," strange atmospheric conditions bring giant advertising statues to life. In "Nightmare on Evergreen Terrace," Groundskeeper Willie is killed in a freak accident and seeks revenge in the childrens' dreams. In the final segment, Homer steps through a secret portal and becomes three-dimensional.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror VI

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E07. King-size Homer.mp4
items.summary: Mr. Burns institutes a new calisthenics program at work. Most employees enjoy the morning workout, except Homer, who is too lazy. He finds out that if he goes in disability, he will be exempt from the exercises. He finds hyper-obesity among the list of disability, so he gorges himself on food to balloon up to 300 pounds.
items.title: King-Size Homer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E08. Mother Simpson.mp4
items.summary: To get out of cleaning a park as community service, Homer fakes his own death. When this results in the family's utilities being cut off, Marge puts pressure on him to reveal that he is alive. However, the spurious news of his "death" brings his long-lost mother - a hippie who is on the run from the law because of her activism against Mr. Burns - back to Springfield.
items.title: Mother Simpson

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E09. Sideshow Bob's Last Gleaming.mp4
items.summary: After Sideshow Bob escapes from prison, the Springfield Air Show is the setting for his ill-fated vendetta against television and Krusty the Clown.
items.title: Sideshow Bob's Last Gleaming

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E10. The Simpsons 138th Episode Spectacular.mp4
items.summary: Troy McClure hosts a behind-the-scenes look at the show, including clips of the series' beginnings as shorts on "The Tracy Ullman Show," Simpsons trivia questions, and unaired scenes from popular episodes.
items.title: The Simpsons 138th Episode Spectacular

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E11. Marge Be Not Proud.mp4
items.summary: Nabbed for shoplifting, Bart manages to keep it a secret from the family... until it's time to have the family Christmas photo taken at the Try-N-Save.
items.title: Marge Be Not Proud

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E12. Team Homer.mp4
items.summary: Homer catches Mr. Burns in an ether-induced haze and asks for $500 for his bowling team. When Burns' head clears, he demands to join the team. Meanwhile, Bart's inflammatory T-shirt provokes Principal Skinner to require school uniforms.
items.title: Team Homer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E13. Two Bad Neighbors.mp4
items.summary: To avoid politics, former President George Bush and his wife Barbara retire to Springfield, citing its low voter turnout. They quickly become friends to the conservative Flanders family, but George soon becomes the enemy of Bart and Homer Simpson.
items.title: Two Bad Neighbors

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E14. Scenes From The Class Struggle In Springfield.mp4
items.summary: After Grandpa destroys their television set, the Simpsons go to an outlet mall to buy a new one. Marge decides to peruse a clothing store, and buys a discounted Chanel suit. A chance encounter with a High School acquaintance, while wearing the suit, leads to an invitation to join a country club. Marge becomes obsessed with pleasing the club's upper-class clientÃ¨le to so she can be accepted.
items.title: Scenes from the Class Struggle in Springfield
items.titleSort: Scenes from the Class Struggle in Springfield

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E15. Bart The Fink.mp4
items.summary: In a scheme to get Krusty's autograph, Bart sends him a check. When Krusty's offshore holding corporation endorses the check, his illegal tax shelter is exposed. In despair after the government auctions off his possessions, Krusty fakes his own death.
items.title: Bart the Fink

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E16. Lisa The Iconoclast.mp4
items.summary: While researching into Jebediah Springfield's past for an essay, Lisa discovers that the town founder wasn't the hero that everyone thinks he was.
items.title: Lisa the Iconoclast

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E17. Homer The Smithers.mp4
items.summary: Burns's personal assistant Smithers goes on holiday and Homer is chosen to be his stand-in. However he is so useless that Burns learns to cope for himself, making Smithers redundant when he returns to Springfield. Smithers and Homer get into a fight, during which Burns is thrown through a window. This means that he will now be very reliant on Smithers after all.
items.title: Homer the Smithers

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E18. The Day The Violence Died.mp4
items.summary: Bart meets the original animator who created Itchy, penniless some 70 years after the studio stole his idea. When Bart helps him sue for restitution, he unwittingly bankrupts Itchy & Scratchy.
items.title: The Day the Violence Died

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E19. A Fish Called Selma.mp4
items.summary: Washed-up movie star Troy McClure is pulled over for driving without corrective lenses, and forced to go to the DMV to get his eyes checked. While there, he meets Selma, who he asks out for dinner. Spotted by a reporter, he quickly realizes that being seen in public with a woman will grab enough headlines to revitalize his career, leading to a whirlwind romance between him and Selma.
items.title: A Fish Called Selma

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E20. Bart On The Road.mp4
items.summary: Bart creates a fake driver's license for himself and uses it to go on a spring break road trip with Milhouse, Nelson, and Martin. Meanwhile, Homer and Lisa bond after spending some quality time together at work.
items.title: Bart on the Road

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E21. 22 Short Films About Springfield.mp4
items.summary: Bart and Milhouse wonder if anything interesting happens to the citizens of Springfield, which leads to a series of interconnected vignettes.
items.title: 22 Short Films About Springfield

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E22. Raging Abe Simpson And His Grumbling Grandson In 'the Curse Of The Flying Hellfish'.mp4
items.summary: When a fellow veteran dies, Grandpa Simpson and Mr. Burns fight for buried WWII treasure as the only surviving members of their battalion.
items.title: Raging Abe Simpson and His Grumbling Grandson in 'The Curse of the Flying Hellfish'
items.titleSort: Raging Abe Simpson and His Grumbling Grandson in 'The Curse of the Flying Hellfish'

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E23. Much Apu About Nothing.mp4
items.summary: When Mayor Quimby uses immigrants as a political scapegoat, the Simpsons discover that Apu is an illegal immigrant.
items.title: Much Apu About Nothing

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E24. Homerpalooza.mp4
items.summary: To show his kids how hip he is, Homer takes Bart and Lisa to a music festival, where he earns himself a place in the sideshow by catching a cannonball with his belly.
items.title: Homerpalooza

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 07/S07E25. Summer Of 4 Ft. 2.mp4
items.summary: The end of the school year, and an empty yearbook causes Lisa to contemplate her lack of popularity. When Ned Flanders is summoned for jury duty and offers Homer a chance to stay at his beach house, Lisa sees this as the opportunity to reinvent herself as a slacker in the hope of gaining friends, which proves to be far more successful than she could possibly imagine --- but not if Bart has any say in the matter.
items.title: Summer of 4 Ft. 2

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E01. Treehouse Of Horror Vii.mp4
items.summary: A Halloween trilogy. This time, Bart meets his "pure evil" Siamese twin; Lisa's science project attacks Bart; aliens Kang and Kodos invade as Clinton and Dole's replicas just before the 1996 Presidential election.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror VII

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E02. You Only Move Twice.mp4
items.summary: In an idyllic planned community, Homer works for a new boss who has trouble with the government. Meanwhile, the rest of the family has difficulty dealing with the bucolic burg.
items.title: You Only Move Twice

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E03. The Homer They Fall.mp4
items.summary: When Moe sees that Homer can absorb massive blows to the head, he turns him into a prizefighter and sets up a match with heavyweight champion Drederick Tatum.
items.title: The Homer They Fall

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E04. Burns, Baby Burns.mp4
items.summary: The Simpsons give a lift to a man called Larry who is hitching to Springfield after discovering that he is Burns's long-lost son. Burns is initially happy to see him but tires of Larry's uncouth slobbishness and Larry is befriended by Homer. He decides that Larry might win back his father's love by means of a fake kidnapping. The plan is exposed but Burns forgives Larry, who then goes home to his wife and children.
items.title: Burns, Baby Burns

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E05. Bart After Dark.mp4
items.summary: Whilst Marge and Lisa are at the coast helping to clean up after an oil spill, Bart, left to his own devices, comes upon a house of ill repute and soon ends up working on the door. Marge is appalled to find that Homer knew but did nothing to stop his son and leads a deputation of local citizens demanding its closure, culminating in her accidentally bull-dozing it.
items.title: Bart After Dark

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E06. A Milhouse Divided.mp4
items.summary: At a party at the Simpsons' house, Milhouse's parents Luann and Kirk publicly row and later split up, Kirk having to go and live at a motel while Luann takes up with younger Gladiator Chase. Fearing that his own marriage is in jeopardy, Homer divorces Marge so that he can remarry her properly and with ceremony in front of all their friends. Kirk attempts the same with Luann but fails.
items.title: A Milhouse Divided

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E07. Lisa's Date With Density.mp4
items.summary: Lisa develops a crush on Nelson and tries to change him into a better person. Meanwhile, Homer finds an autodialer and starts a telemarketing scam.
items.title: Lisa's Date with Density

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E08. Hurricane Neddy.mp4
items.summary: A hurricane destroys the Flanders' home and they have to move into the church basement. The people of Springfield gather to rebuild their house, but when Ned sees the poor workmanship, he has a complete breakdown.
items.title: Hurricane Neddy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E09. El Viaje De Nuestro Jomer (the Mysterious Voyage Of Homer).mp4
items.summary: After eating a dish laced with potent peppers during the chili cookoff, Homer has hallucinations where a mystical coyote urges him to find his soulmate.
items.title: El Viaje Misterioso de Nuestro Jomer (The Mysterious Voyage of Homer)
items.titleSort: Viaje Misterioso de Nuestro Jomer (The Mysterious Voyage of Homer)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E10. The Springfield Files.mp4
items.summary: Homer witnesses something out of this world in Springfield woods, but no one believes him -- not even FBI agents Fox Mulder and Dana Scully, who come to investigate the incident.
items.title: The Springfield Files

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E11. The Twisted World Of Marge Simpson.mp4
items.summary: Marge goes to work for Frank Ormond,making and selling pretzels and,when he dies,sets up in business for herself. Initially sales are poor until Homer brings in local Mafia boss Fat Tony as her business partner. Sales boom as a result but,unfortunately,any profits vanish due to Fat Tony's 'business agreement' with Homer.
items.title: The Twisted World of Marge Simpson

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E12. Mountain Of Madness.mp4
items.summary: Burns takes his staff to Mount Useful for a team-building exercise,the object being to reach a cabin at the top. Paired with Homer,Burns cheats and they reach their destination but experience cabin fever when snowed in by an avalanche. Eventually Homer uses a propane stove to turn the cabin into a sled that sends them back to safety.
items.title: Mountain of Madness

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E13. Simpsoncalifragilisticexpiala (annoyed Grunt) Cious.mp4
items.summary: Marge Simpson is starting to lose hair due to the stress of running the Simpson household. The family decide to get a nanny and are approached by Shary Bobbins, a Mary Poppins figure in Victorian attire, complete with a flying umbrella. The British nanny seems to bring joy to everyone with her London music hall style singing and eccentric charm. Yet working in the Simpson household soon starts to cause problems for the kindly nursemaid.
items.title: Simpsoncalifragilisticexpiala (Annoyed Grunt) cious

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E14. The Itchy & Scratchy & Poochie Show.mp4
items.summary: In an attempt to boost ratings, the Itchy and Scratchy Show adds a new "in-your-face" character voiced by Homer.
items.title: The Itchy & Scratchy & Poochie Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E15. Homer's Phobia.mp4
items.summary: Homer fears that Bart's masculinity is at stake when he suspects he is being influenced by a flamboyant homosexual collectible store owner named John. All his efforts to show Bart how to be a man keep backfiring on him... or do they?
items.title: Homer's Phobia

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E16. The Brother From Another Series.mp4
items.summary: Sideshow Bob is released from prison into the custody of his younger brother Cecil (voiced by David Hyde Pierce), Springfield's Chief Hydrological Engineer. He works as the foreman on a new hydroelectric dam. Bart is convinced that Bob is up to something shady again, and follows him everywhere.
items.title: Brother from Another Series

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E17. My Sister, My Sitter.mp4
items.summary: Lisa becomes in demand as a baby-sitter so,when Marge and Homer,attend the opening of the Squidport quay,they leave her in charge at home. An angry Bart plays her up,resulting in his dislocating an arm and bumping his head and Lisa bundles him off to the hospital with Maggie in tow. They end up at Squidport where Lisa is mortified that people should think her incompetent but,after Bart apologises,she ends up back in business.
items.title: My Sister, My Sitter

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E18. Homer Vs. The Eighteenth Amendment.mp4
items.summary: Bart gets drunk during a St. Patrick's Day Parade, provoking the city to enforce a two-hundred year old prohibition law. Rex Banner, an Elliot Ness-type character, takes over the police force to help enforce the law since Wiggum has failed to do so. Meanwhile, Homer decides to make money for himself as a bootlegger, and is soon nicknamed "The Beer Baron".
items.title: Homer vs. the Eighteenth Amendment

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E19. Grade School Confidential.mp4
items.summary: Bart discovers Principal Skinner and Mrs. Krabappel kissing, and it's not long before the whole town knows of their secret affair.
items.title: Grade School Confidential

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E20. The Canine Mutiny.mp4
items.summary: When Bart can't pay the credit card bill for his expensive new purebred dog, the repo men unwittingly take Santa's Little Helper.
items.title: The Canine Mutiny

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E21. The Old Man And The Lisa.mp4
items.summary: When Burns is declared bankrupt,Lisa shows him how to make money out of recycling on condition that he becomes a full convert and renounces his grasping ways. The recycling plant is a success but he reneges on the deal to catch marine life to make 'Li'l Lisa Slurry'. Lisa refuses to take any of the profits and he sells the plant on.
items.title: The Old Man and the Lisa

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E22. In Marge We Trust.mp4
items.summary: Disturbed that Reverend Lovejoy has lost interest in counseling parishioners, Marge volunteers as the "Listen Lady." Meanwhile, Homer sees his likeness on a box of Japanese detergent.
items.title: In Marge We Trust

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E23. Homer's Enemy.mp4
items.summary: A hardworking new employee at the power plant is consumed with resentment at Homer's undeserved success.
items.title: Homer's Enemy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E24. The Simpsons Spin-off Showcase.mp4
items.summary: Troy McClure presents three Simpsons spinoff spoofs: In "Chief Wiggum, P.I.," Chief Wiggum becomes a New Orleans detective. Next, Grampa Simpson's soul is trapped inside Moe's Love tester machine in "The Love-Matic Grampa." Finally, the Simpson family hosts a '70s-style variety show.
items.title: The Simpsons Spin-Off Showcase

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 08/S08E25. The Secret War Of Lisa Simpson.mp4
items.summary: Lisa joins the all-male military school where Bart is sent for discipline. Then comes the hazing.
items.title: The Secret War of Lisa Simpson

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 09/S09E01. The City Of New York Vs. Homer Simpson.mp4
items.summary: Designated driver Barney absconds to Manhattan in Homer's car and leaves it there. But when the family journeys to the Big Apple to retrieve their property, Homer discovers his car has been booted.
items.title: The City of New York vs. Homer Simpson
items.titleSort: City of New York vs. Homer Simpson

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 09/S09E02. The Principal And The Pauper.mp4
items.summary: Unmasked as an impostor, Principal Skinner flees to Capital City to reclaim his former life as a shiftless good-for-nothing. The people of Springfield gain a newfound appreciation for him and form a plan to bring him back.
